@NODE "mail_51" " Re: dim before statement/function "
From: Nick Clover <bauk@...>
Date: 08-19-02 17:28:26
Subject: @{b}Re: dim before statement/function@{ub}

Hello Joar

On 19-Aug-02, you wrote:

Try this:

Dim dimming(3)
Statement dumdidei{a}
shared dimming
dimming(1)=a+1          <--...array not yet dimmed
dimming(2)=a+2
dimming(3)=a+3
End Statement
b=4
dumdidei{b}
End

> why do I get that error?

You get the error because statements and functions use 'local' variables
that are cleared when you exit the statement/function, you must tell the 
statement it can use your dimmed variable with the shared command...

